	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Addis Ababa - The leaders of the United Nations and the African Union urged stronger international cooperation at the opening on Sunday of the African Union summit in the Ethiopian capital, Addis Ababa. UN Secretary-General Antonio Guterres said he strongly believes Africa is one of the greatest forces for good in the world. He said he wants to mobilize greater support for UN peacekeeping forces in Africa, including those battling extremist violence in Somalia, Nigeria and in West Africa. African Union Commission chairperson Moussa Faki Mahamat warned against the "rise of national egoism," which some took as a veiled reference to US President Donald Trump. The summit is expected to issue a response to Trump's recent comment in which he likened African countries to a filthy toilet. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  